text: To make way for the Bank of America- Swank Franks has closed. I didn't really get to enjoy this place as much as my friends did, but it guess i will miss it. Their fried mushrooms were awesome. And  I dont know if it's true or not...but i hear they are moving to Logan Square!

So the Frank is shutting down its Wicker Park operation and moving to Logan Square. Drat. I hope they open a bank in that space. The casing of their Chicago dogs snapped the loudest when you bit into 'em. It sounded like your knuckle broke.  One star for sadness.

Traditional Chicago hot dog stand, open late, fast service, and good location. What's not to love?  Well, sometimes there are vagrants about, but whatever... Really though, only one thing - no bathroom. That door you thought was a bathroom? I went in it, and it took me down a winding staircase to a seriously creepy basement... Don't go in there.

Long live the veggie dog!  Worth noting: Frank must be religious because he's closed on Sundays (boooo). THIS JUST IN... SWANK FRANKS IS RUMORED TO BE CLOSING AT THE END OF 2007 TO MAKE WAY FOR A BANK OF AMERICA.  I'M HATING!!!

The only thing I can say about this place is that they have fried twinkies...that is all I had when I went in. I had heard about the Fried Twinkie and being a fan of all things sweet I went and tried one...I loved it.

Mmmm . . . low and behold a drunkards paradise! Its about 4am or so and my friends and I stumble  into this fine establishment (nearly swaying from  side to side in an attempt to hold up the walls) and we ordered the most ridiculous items. Fried everything. Gross I know . . . but delicious. Let's talk about the  fried twinkies . . .  You may be apprehensive about it at first, but trust in me when I say this: At first bite, your taste buds will do backflips. I loved it!

I was so happy when this place re-opened with VEGGIE DOGS on the menu! Basically that's why I'm giving it 4 stars. This is just a standard fast-food place, but they do have a good amount of options with hush puppies and sweet potato fries on the menu. I mostly just go here for the veggie dog, which is actually really good I think mostly to the yummy bun that they use. However avoid the veggie burger at all costs, they are thin and taste gross.

They have veggie dogs and they're GOOD!  Yes, thats right, they don't taste like sponge and when you add some ketchup, onions and pickles it's a drunk vegetarian's dream, ahhhh.  The onion rings were decent but my friends said the cheese fries were not so hot.  Stick to the dogs, whether they're the veggie or 'real' variety!
Good place to get a drunk dog. I dig the chardog & fries, and I've actually eaten here when I wasn't drunk and they were good.   Deep-fried Twinkie.  Sounds interesting.

The food isn't bad, but since they went under new management the service is utterly incompetent. Going there after midnight on a weekend is not worth the frustration unless you're blackout-drunk.  I went here every weekend night for a year or so before the new management, and was always pleased, and since the new crew arrived I have yet to receive the right order after an inevitable half-hour wait.

EDIT (04-19-07): This place is now CLOSED! Don't get me wrong, I preferred the hot dogs and pizza from the Underdog cart outside Flash Taco (directly across the street), but this place had pretty decent food. And what are they putting in its place? A Bank of America. There's already another bank across the fucking street. Man... Eat shit.  ~*~*~*~*~*~ Their cheese fries are good. So are their mozerella sticks, as well as their gyros. Awesome greasy food to cut the aftermath of binge drinking. Heck, I've had these 3 menu items sober and they're still pretty good. Kinda overpriced. I've had stuff comparable for cheaper. But, when you're drunk, you fork over the money for insanely delicious, greasy food.

My love for hotdogs aside, Swank Frank is bitchin' because it's the only place I've found that serves fried Twinkies outside of good ol' Louisiana.  Yeah, I said it--I ate a fried Twinkie, with my dad no less, the fellow who has crossed gluten and white sugar and dairy off his Christmas card list (and no, it wasn't because of the Twinkie). Sugar + fat + fried +chocolate sauce and/or powdered sugar = disgustingly indulgent.  It's like looking death in the face, shrugging your shoulders with indifference and continuing down your path of damnation.  It tastes good, sort of... warm, gooey, sweet--but you can't help have the nagging sensation that 10 years of your life just went down the drain in a giant glob of trans fats. Anyhoo, eating a fried Twinkie is a surefire way to get your daily caloric allowance while upping your chance for a massive heart attack.  Actually, I might be wrong about the caloric allowance part because, I ain't gonna lie, this thing makes its way out shortly after it's made its way in.

Like the new decor. You know? Yah, er. I do stop by for a veggie hot dog occassionally and a tray of some sort of overly-greasy treats. The last time I was there I had a veggie dog, Chicago-style and a fairie, it had to be, lightly dusted the thing with celery salt---amazing. So simple. So good.

Fantastic burgers priced for drunk people with more money than sense.  Alas, poor Wickerdog, we knew ye well. You were disgusting and probably violated at least a dozen health codes but at least you could get a couple hot dogs and fries for less than five bucks.

Bring on the cheese! OK... I know it's hot dogs...  but I have to give this guy 5 stars.  They use REAL cheese for their menu items.  Not the powder plus water, squeeze can or other bag form of cheese substance. It's for real... Merkts all the way!  This is a good hot dog joint whether intoxicated or just in the mood to pick up a red hot...

This was the group's last stop this past Friday evening.  I have to say, as hot dog joints go, Swank Frank's is right up there.  If you've been to a Chicago hot dog stand, then you know the menu.  I don't need to tell it to you.  Is there a law that dictates what these places serve? What I liked about Swank Frank's was the dude behind the counter.  This guy actually took joy in conversing with the drunk asses, rather then loath them.  Our group, collectively probably did 3 Jager-bombs a piece, so we were all lit and somewhat confused about our order.  The guy behind the counter was patient and helped us remember what we had ordered, not 10 minutes prior. I'll definitely be going back.  Good times.
Fried Twinkies!  Oh, and they have really good veggie burgers too.

I work 2nd shift and there are those 24 hour and late night centers.  Swank Frank is a great 2:00am option, and the people who eat there are generally bus and blue line riders not bums. I've only had a burger since their remodel which makes them look retro instead of just run down.  I probably would never eat here before midnight but once the restaurants are shut down this is an awesome place to grab a fanta grape soda and a Gyro. Speaking of the Gyro, aka. the belt buster, this is bigger and better tasting then any Gyro in Greek Town (they fry the bread a bit, yum!). Since their remodel I notice they've posted quite a few vegan and healthy oriented items to their menu.  I believe I saw a Jerked Chicken Sandwich on Ciabatta, I will post another review after trying that.

If you wanna feel naughty, peek in the windows on the corner of Damen & North and watch the people who actually GO here and actually BUY something cooked in that kitchen and actually EAT it. The weenies are long and smooth, and the patrons are always short and hairy. Ew! A bum just touched my butt! I should move along.

Good for late night bar food...mainly because you are drunk.  A sober person wouldn't eat a heartburn dog at 2am.  Plus, the very thought of a deep fried twinkie is just plain disgusting...sober OR drunk.  I cringe everytime I see that sign when I drive by.
Just the thought of a deep fried Twinke makes me want to take a shower.
I had a great polish with onions and fries here, they actually have a much bigger selection then most hotdog places,  ill be back again thats for sure
You can't pass through Bucktown and not go here for a fried candy bar!  They are the perfect snack and compliment to one of this place's enormous hot dogs!
